title: Grateful Dead Live at Laguna Seca Recreation Area on 1988-07-29
lineage: 3rd gen sbd > NakCR-3A > AudigySE > Audacity > CDwave > TLH
description:
Set 2(ONLY)

China Cat Sunflower-> Crazy Fingers-> I Know You Rider-> Playin' In The Band-> Drums-> Space-> The Wheel-> Gimme Some Lovin'-> Believe It Or Not-> Sugar Magnolia, E: Black Muddy River

reviews.review_text: Just lovely. Thanks for the upload.  They pull of the China>Crazy>Rider without too much slop or hesitation.  Once that effort is past, they let loose w/ an intensely drippy and trippy Playin'.......

a rare and different set This is the only China>Crazy Fingers>Know You Rider they ever played.  I thought I had that sequence from a different venue, but deadbase says no.  Combined with Believe it or not [not exactly a stellar piece, but not very common either] in the Jerry slot this gets high marks just for uniqueness.

5 stars from a tough year Seeing the Boys on the East Coast for the Early summer shows I was impressed. But then in Landover, MD and MSG in the Fall, the shows fell to be average- at best.

This  Mid-Summer Show is a cooker. Much has already been made about the Playin - and really that is the essence of the show. It has no peer post '85, imho.

Of course, the China>Crazy>Rider is a gem for uniqueness. (I remember being thrilled since they had not done much other to alter the normal sequence of china>rider-- sans China>Cumberland and 1/2 step>Rider back in '85.).

The reason I wrote 'tough year', is that aside from shows already mentioned, the band seemed to Fall into a "go out and do it" routine. And a low point (which I know had good intentions) was the 9/24/88 MSG show.

If you want a great one from '88 this is top 3. 

God Bless and Enjoy.

reaching for a gold ring Little background hiss on this one..but..not bad. 88' was a strange year with not to many shows that stand out. What really hits you which has already been mentioned, is the Crazy fingers sandwiched between the China>Rider..WOW..that alone carries weight. Also a version of Believe it or Not which did not get played often. A fun little 2nd set here..GIVE IT A WHIRL
